subSubSection.paragraph:
Such 'over spitting' of generic taxa inhabiting Japan has also been documented in the pulmonate family Clausiliidae , which is a character-rich family such as the Alycaeidae (
Pall-Gergely et al. 2019
). Nordsieck (1998) stated that the Japanese clausiliid genera and subgenera correspond only to subgenera and species groups of Western Palaearctic clausiliids. This claim was confirmed by recent molecular phylogeny ( Motochin et al. 2017 ).
